		" 
			>
			<DIV>NEW IDEAS!!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You are all missing the key to mages... Summoning!&nbsp; This is precisely why our class is unbalanced.&nbsp; Items like armor, weapons and focus gear get better and better with each expansion, but do mage summoned items? No!&nbsp; This is the biggest problem for sure.&nbsp; No one has mentioned our summoned gear, you know why? No one uses or cares about it, our weapons and armor suck, you can buy better gear for your pets in the baz and make back the money faster than you could cast.&nbsp; I have so many useless summoning spells now.&nbsp; Those need upgrades.&nbsp; We should have nice armor with nice effects for our pets, effects that heal them and give them bigger damage and such, and we should be able to tell when it is on, we should be able to manage pets inventory.&nbsp; I understand this last idea is a bit big, but honestly what if you want your pet to switch from a fire proc weapon to an ice or wind, gotta kill it and make all new gear? Kinda lame.&nbsp; And on charmed pets you get gear back, if we are such great pet classes why don't we even have that ability?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>ANOTHER IDEA!!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We are&nbsp;defensless upon zone-in.&nbsp; All other pet based classes have a chance when they zone in.&nbsp; Beasts and Shadow Knights have the HP to take a coulple hits, Necro's can simply feign death, Wizards can snare and run away, what do mages have?&nbsp; Gate?&nbsp; Thats not enough, gate takes to long and is too easily interupted, gating is only helpful if pet can off-tank the mob.&nbsp; But when we zone in we have no pet. This is a problem.&nbsp; I am so sick of zoning in or getting a res and always being the one that the mob goes for first, and I am not exagerating, I always always always take the first hit from a roamer, or entrance mob.&nbsp; This is a lame setup considering I have the lowest hitpoints of anyone I know and I have no defense without a pet.&nbsp; Anyone care to comment, is there some emergency skill that us mages have that I am not aware of?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>YOUR POINTS!!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There are awesome points throughout this thread, I almost cried when I heard my cleric friend could nuke 9 times on one mana bar while soloing with the nukes landing for 1100 and she was still able to heal herself, the 2nd best nuker in the game can't out nuke a cleric? Thats crap and so I agree that nukes should be bigger and mana cost should be lower.&nbsp; Also focus items are fun and all but they are items and have little to do with class balancing in the way we are discussing it here, at least thats how I see it.&nbsp; Lheo... you seem fairly clueless, you are talking up mages with absolutely no evidence, you obviously didn't read the opening to this post but I suppose thats your thing.&nbsp;&nbsp; The thing is mages shouldn't have to worry about focus items we should summon them.&nbsp; </DIV>	
